SUMMARY:🍳 Breakfast: Savory Oatmeal
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Savory Oatmeal\nServings: 1\nPrep: 5 min | Cook: 10 min | Total: 15 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 1.0 clove garlic, minced\n• 0.5 tsp grated fresh ginger\n• 4.0 mushrooms\n• 1.0 tsp vegan butter (Earth Balance)\n• 1.0 cup vegetable broth\n• 0.5 cup old-fashioned rolled oats\n• 0.5 cup spinach\n• 0.5 tsp toasted sesame oil\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Mince the garlic, grate the ginger, and slice the mushrooms.\n2. Add the butter, garlic, and ginger to a small saucepot. Sauté over medium heat for 1-2 minutes.\n3. Add the mushrooms and continue to sauté for a few minutes more, or until the mushrooms have wilted a bit.\n4. Add the vegetable broth to the saucepot, turn the heat up to medium-high, and bring the broth up to a boil.\n5. When the broth reaches a boil, add the rolled oats and stir to combine. Allow it to return to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium low. Let the oats simmer for about 5 minutes, or until thickened.\n6. While the oats are simmering, roughly chop the spinach. Stir the spinach into the thickened oats, along with the toasted sesame oil.\n7. Taste and add salt to your liking, if needed, then top it off with your favorite toppings. Serve hot!\n\nTip: 🥛 DAIRY-FREE SWAPS: butter → vegan butter (Earth Balance). Savory oatmeal is a delicious, hearty, and inexpensive meal that can be customized to use ingredients you have on hand.\n\nSource: https://www.budgetbytes.com/savory-oatmeal/
IMAGE;VALUE=URI:https://www.budgetbytes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Savory-Oatmeal-above.jpg
URL:https://www.budgetbytes.com/savory-oatmeal/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mealplan-20260518-lunch-2@mealplanner
DTSTAMP:20260518T142617Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260518T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260518T130000
SUMMARY:🥗 Lunch: Peanut Noodles with Chicken
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Peanut Noodles with Chicken\nServings: 4\nPrep: 10 min | Cook: 15 min | Total: 25 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 0.333 cup smooth natural-style peanut butter\n• 2.0 tbsp sriracha\n• 2.0 tbsp brown sugar\n• 1.0 fresh lime\n• 1.0 tbsp soy sauce\n• 1.0 clove garlic, minced\n• 1.0 tsp grated fresh ginger\n• 1.0 13.5 oz. can coconut milk\n• 1.0 boneless, skinless chicken breast\n• 1.0 tbsp cooking oil\n• 8.0 oz noodles*\n• 0.25 cup chopped peanuts\n• 0.25 cup chopped cilantro\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Prepare the peanut sauce first. In a medium bowl, whisk together the peanut butter, sriracha, brown sugar, soy sauce, 2 Tbsp lime juice, minced garlic, and grated ginger.\n2. Add the coconut milk to the peanut sauce and whisk until smooth again.\n3. Cut the chicken breast into small ½ to 1-inch sized pieces.\n4. Heat a large skillet over medium-high. Once hot, add the cooking oil and swirl to coat the surface of the skillet. Add the chicken and cook until browned on all sides. Be careful not to overcook the chicken.\n5. Add the prepared peanut sauce into the skillet, turn the heat down to medium-low, and stir to dissolve any browned bits off the bottom of the skillet. Let the chicken simmer in the sauce over low, stirring occasionally, while you cook the noodles.\n6. Cook your noodles according to the package directions, then drain in a colander.\n7. Add the cooked and drained noodles to the skillet with the peanut sauce and chicken. Toss until everything is evenly mixed and coated in sauce.\n8. Top the noodles with chopped peanuts and cilantro, then enjoy!\n\nTip: These Peanut Noodles with Chicken are an easy meal with a rich, creamy, sweet, and savory flavor that is completely addictive.\n\nSource: https://www.budgetbytes.com/peanut-noodles-with-chicken/
IMAGE;VALUE=URI:https://www.budgetbytes.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Peanut-Noodles-with-Chicken-close.jpg
URL:https://www.budgetbytes.com/peanut-noodles-with-chicken/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
